.TH CAIGED-CONNECT 1 "February 2026" "caiged" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
caiged-connect \- Connect to an OpenCode server with the TUI client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B caiged connect
\fIproject-name\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B caiged connect
launches the OpenCode TUI client connected to a running container by project name. This allows you to connect to any running caiged container from any directory without needing to navigate to the project directory.
.PP
The command searches for a running container matching the project name, retrieves its connection information, and launches
.BR opencode\ attach
with the appropriate URL and credentials.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I project-name
The project name or slug to connect to. This can be the full project name (e.g., "my-app") or any portion that uniquely identifies the container.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Connect to a project named "my-app":
.B caiged connect my-app
.TP
Connect to a project with a complex name:
.B caiged connect code-myproject
.SH CONTAINER NAMING
Containers are named using the format:
.B caiged-{spin}-{project}
.PP
The connect command searches for containers where the project portion matches the provided argument.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B no running container found for project
No container matching the provided project name was found. Use
.B caiged session list
to see all running containers.
.TP
.B no port found for container
The container exists but doesn't have port information in its labels. This may indicate an older container using legacy configuration.
